The jiraportlet macro takes up about 95% of a processor.  
It comes from this code below running every second.  

jQuery(function($) {
    $("div.jiraportlet").each(function() {
        setInterval("jiraportlet.makePortletLinksOpenInParentWindow()", 1000);
        setInterval("jiraportlet.resizeIframes()", 1000); /* Resize every second, because we don't know when all the CSS in an iframe will finish loading */
    });
});

h5. Bug Details
When the following Wiki markup is included in a page, the link does not work in Internet Explorer:
{code}
[!ImageName.gif|align=right!|PagetoLink]
{code}

h5. Possible reason
# Starting from Confluence 3.0, the use of float has been introduced which is used in conjunction with the style attribute:
{quote}
<p><a href="/display/test/PagetoLink" title="PagetoLink"><span class="image-wrap" *style="float: right"*><img src="/download/attachments/19562498/ImageName.gif?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1257348447075" border="0" /></span></a></p>
{quote}
# Prior to Confluence 3.0, the align property was used:
{quote}
<p><a href="/conf/display/test/PagetoLink" title="PagetoLink"><img src="/conf/download/attachments/21299276/ImageName.gif" *align="right"* border="0" /></a></p>
{quote}

h5. Link to IE Bug
