Our first install of Confluence was early 2007. Since then we have upgraded several times, but the Demonstration Space has stayed the same since when it was installed. I'm sure this space has had the UI enhanced as well as gives helpful documentation and examples to users, so I would prefer to be able to upgrade this space to the most current content that ships with our latest version of Confluence.

I have searched to try and find how to do this but I have not been able to find if there's already a method. I wouldn't mind to just delete the space and re-create from an XML backup. Maybe during upgrade there could be an option to re-deploy the demonstration space. Could a possible workaround be to delete the demonstration space before upgrading, and upon upgrading the latest version will be added?

Thanks

