In Confluence 2.8, the following search map worked fine:
{code}
my $search_map = {
         spaceKey => "ds",
         type => "blogpost",
         modified => ""
         };
{code}

resulted in

{noformat}
$VAR1 = [
          {
            'excerpt' => 'abazaba',
            'url' => 'http://localhost:8080/display/ds/2009/10/28/testingNews',
            'title' => 'testingNews',
            'type' => 'blogpost',
            'id' => '393219'
          }
        ];
{noformat}

In Confluence 3.0.2 it no longer works and results in an undefined result set.
{noformat}
$VAR1 = undef;
{noformat}

In both versions, if you use the [documented|http://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Remote+API+Specification#RemoteAPISpecification-Search] values everything works fine.

